HB 3623 By Representatives BARTON, J SMITH, Senator ROSENBAUM; Representatives KOMP, MATTHEWS, Senators BATES, BONAMICI, BOQUIST, BURDICK, COURTNEY, DEVLIN, DINGFELDER, EDWARDS, JOHNSON, MONNES ANDERSON, MONROE, MORRISETTE, PROZANSKI, SCHRADER, SHIELDS, STARR, TELFER, VERGER, WHITSETT, WINTERS (Presession filed.) -- Relating to human trafficking information; and declaring an emergency.
02/01 (H) First reading. Referred to Speaker's desk.
02/01 (H) Referred to Human Services.
02/03 (H) Public Hearing and Work Session held.
02/05 (H) Work Session held.
02/05 (H) Recommendation: Do pass with amendments and be printed A-Engrossed.
02/08 (H) Second reading.
02/09 (H) Third reading. Carried by Barton. Passed. Ayes, 59; Excused, 1--Clem.
02/10 (S) First reading. Referred to President's desk.
02/11 (S) Referred to Human Services and Rural Health Policy.
02/16 (S) Public Hearing and Work Session held.
02/17 (S) Recommendation: Do pass the A-Eng. bill.
02/17 (S) Second reading.
02/18 (S) Carried over to 02-19 by unanimous consent.
02/19 (S) Third reading. Carried by Rosenbaum. Passed. Ayes, 30.
02/23 (H) Speaker signed.
02/23 (S) President signed.
03/18 (H) Governor signed.
03/18 (H) Chapter 65, (2010 Laws): Effective date March 18, 2010.
